Caption: bloated linux distro
Picture depicts a rotund penguin.

Tux the penguin is often used as a general symbol of the kernel and distro. This
post mocks distros that are "bloated" and take a lot of hardware resources to
operate.

Now, AOSC OS isn't exactly known to be disk-space friendly...
*slaps my storage server* "This bad boy can fit so many penguins in it."
